---
description: Velarro security guardrails for app code, headers, CSP, cookies, third-party assets, forms, and security-sensitive documentation.
globs: ["app/**", "components/**", "lib/security/**", "lib/age/**", "next.config.ts", "tests/security/**", "tests/e2e/**", "docs/implementation/modules/M00-hardening/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

For every Velarro implementation task, apply security from the start.

Do not expose secrets, API keys, tokens, private URLs, credentials, or environment values in client code.

Do not weaken Content Security Policy or security headers to make implementation easier.

Do not add unapproved third-party scripts, analytics, embeds, fonts, external images, or remote domains.

Do not use dangerouslySetInnerHTML unless explicitly approved, sanitized, and documented.

Do not invent auth, payment, admin, backend, session, privacy, legal, compliance, or backend behavior.

Age-state cookies must store only approved non-PII values.

Every security-relevant change must include or preserve tests where possible.

Before claiming a feature is security-ready, ask the Velarro Security Auditor subagent to review it.
